"{\"uid\": \"straitstimes.com-sport-explainer-olympics-will-the-river-seine-be-suitable-for-swimming-for-the-paris-2024-games\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Choose edition  Search  singapore  asia  world  opinion  life  business  sport  Visual  Podcasts  SPH Rewards  STClassifieds  Paid press releases  Advertise with us  FAQs  Contact us  Sign up now:Get the biggest sports news in your inbox  FILE PHOTO: Paris 2024 Olympics - Paris, France - June 23, 2024 The Eiffel Tower is seen from the water of the Seine River as the Olympics opening ceremony rehearsal is postponed amid rainy weather.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 437, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 98, \"end\": 101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.486921326596675e-14, \"text\": \"SPH\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\"}, {\"begin\": 147, \"end\": 156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"score\": 0.9604822703099307, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Advertise\", \"types\": [\"Q7377\", \"Q729\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"REUTERS/Pawel Kopczynski/File Photo    PublishedJul 29, 2024, 08:34 PM  UpdatedJul 29, 2024, 08:34 PM  PARIS - Pollution levels forced Paris 2024 to cancel a triathlon swimming training session for the second consecutive day on Monday, a day ahead of the men's race.\", \"from\": 438, \"to\": 704, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 573, \"end\": 583, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1129761799196463e-17, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organisers have said they are confident Monday's hot weather will help lower the bacteria count sufficiently enough for the competition to proceed.\", \"from\": 706, \"to\": 853, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A swimmable Seine is a key legacy Games organisers aim to leave behind for Paris residents.\", \"from\": 855, \"to\": 946, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 867, \"end\": 872, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999986016519, \"rank\": 1.3985144885330577e-09, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 930, \"end\": 935, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3811566979912588e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"WHERE DO WE STAND NOW?\", \"from\": 948, \"to\": 970, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Seine was suitable for swimming six days out of seven between July 17-23, data published late last week showed.\", \"from\": 972, \"to\": 1087, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 976, \"end\": 981, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999986016519, \"rank\": 1.3985144885330577e-09, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, unseasonably heavy rainfall on the day of the opening ceremony raised pollution levels.\", \"from\": 1088, \"to\": 1184, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The monitoring group (State and City of Paris), based on Eau de Paris water analysis, publishes weekly results.\", \"from\": 1186, \"to\": 1297, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1226, \"end\": 1231, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3811566979912588e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1243, \"end\": 1255, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eau_de_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Eau de Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eau_de_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eau_de_Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"WHAT ARE THE CONDITIONS FOR THE RIVER TO BE SUITABLE FOR SWIMMING?\", \"from\": 1299, \"to\": 1365, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Testers measure the level of two bacteria - E. coli (Escherichia coli) and Enterococcus faecalis.\", \"from\": 1367, \"to\": 1464, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1420, \"end\": 1436, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Escherichia_coli\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.745605828171014e-26, \"text\": \"Escherichia coli\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Escherichia_coli\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Escherichia_coli\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"E.Coli is a bacteria commonly found in the lower intestine of warm-blooded organisms.\", \"from\": 1466, \"to\": 1551, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1466, \"end\": 1472, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Escherichia_coli\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"E.Coli\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Escherichia_coli\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Escherichia_coli\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Most E.coli strains are harmless, but some can cause serious illness.\", \"from\": 1552, \"to\": 1621, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Symptoms include abdominal cramps, diarrhoea, fever and vomiting.\", \"from\": 1622, \"to\": 1687, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Enterococcus faecalis is a common faecal bacteria, also often used as an indicator of water quality at swimming pools and public beaches.\", \"from\": 1689, \"to\": 1826, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"According to European standards, the safe limit for E. coli is 900 colony-forming units (cfu) per 100 millilitres while the threshold for Enterococcus is 330 cfu/100ml.\", \"from\": 1828, \"to\": 1996, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1966, \"end\": 1978, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Enterococcus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Enterococcus\", \"types\": [\"Q12136\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Enterococcus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Enterococcus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"WHICH FACTORS INFLUENCE THE WATER QUALITY?\", \"from\": 1998, \"to\": 2040, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"According to Benjamin Raigneau, director of water quality at the Paris city hall, four main factors have an impact on water pollution.\", \"from\": 2042, \"to\": 2176, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2055, \"end\": 2063, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Benjamin\", \"score\": 0.9995912148312178, \"rank\": 0.000401491000537106, \"text\": \"Benjamin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q4964182\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Benjamin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Benjamin\"}, {\"begin\": 2107, \"end\": 2122, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/H\\u00f4tel_de_Ville,_Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999991164259, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris city hall\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/H\\u00f4tel_de_Ville,_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/H\\u00f4tel_de_Ville,_Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"- Rainfall.\", \"from\": 2178, \"to\": 2189, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"More rain more pollution runoff.\", \"from\": 2190, \"to\": 2222, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"- UV index.\", \"from\": 2224, \"to\": 2235, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The higher the UV index, the faster the bacteria die,\\\" Raigneau said.\", \"from\": 2236, \"to\": 2306, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2252, \"end\": 2254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ultraviolet\", \"score\": 0.9999995376225502, \"rank\": 4.6020816038992353e-07, \"text\": \"UV\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ultraviolet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ultraviolet\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"- Temperature.\", \"from\": 2308, \"to\": 2322, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The higher the temperature, the faster the bacteria dies.\", \"from\": 2323, \"to\": 2380, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Whether the temperature of the water is 16 degrees Celsius (60 degrees Fahrenheit), or above 22 Celsius (71 F) like it usually is in the summer, it makes a significant difference,\\\" Raigneau said.\", \"from\": 2381, \"to\": 2577, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"- The flow of the river.\", \"from\": 2579, \"to\": 2603, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The faster the flow the higher the pollution.\", \"from\": 2604, \"to\": 2649, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"WHAT HAS BEEN DONE TO IMPROVE THE QUALITY OF THE WATER?\", \"from\": 2651, \"to\": 2706, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris has built an underground reservoir designed to hold 46,000 cubic metres of runoff water during a storm, preventing the runoff flooding the city's antiquated sewage network and allowing untreated waste to flow into the Seine.\", \"from\": 2708, \"to\": 2938, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2708, \"end\": 2713, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3811566979912588e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2932, \"end\": 2937, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999986016519, \"rank\": 1.3985144885330577e-09, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Once the water is collected in the Austerlitz basin - a monster, 30-metre (98-feet) deep structure the size of a dozen Olympic swimming pools - it will be directed to a treatment plant before pouring into the Seine.\", \"from\": 2940, \"to\": 3155, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2975, \"end\": 2985, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gare_d'Austerlitz\", \"score\": 0.997517594355529, \"rank\": 0.002488583254947156, \"text\": \"Austerlitz\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gare_d'Austerlitz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gare_d'Austerlitz\"}, {\"begin\": 3149, \"end\": 3154, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999986016519, \"rank\": 1.3985144885330577e-09, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"HOW IS THE DECISION TO ALLOW SWIMMING MADE?\", \"from\": 3157, \"to\": 3200, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Every afternoon the day before each familiarisation session (athletes' swim) and before each competition, a technical committee meets, bringing together all the players involved in the issue of water quality in the Seine: City of Paris, Paris 2024, the International Federation, regional authorities and Meteo France.\", \"from\": 3202, \"to\": 3519, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3432, \"end\": 3437, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3811566979912588e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3506, \"end\": 3518, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/M\\u00e9t\\u00e9o-France\", \"score\": 0.9999999998472049, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Meteo France\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/M\\u00e9t\\u00e9o-France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/M\\u00e9t\\u00e9o-France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the end of this technical committee meeting, an initial analysis is made of the weather conditions.\", \"from\": 3521, \"to\": 3623, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At 3:30 a.m. on the day of the competition, a final meeting is held with all those players involved.\", \"from\": 3625, \"to\": 3725, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"WHO MAKES THE DECISION?\", \"from\": 3727, \"to\": 3750, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The International Federation involved in the sport.\", \"from\": 3752, \"to\": 3803, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"WHAT IF THE WATER IS NOT SUITABLE FOR SWIMMING?\", \"from\": 3805, \"to\": 3852, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There are contingency days planned for the summer of 2024 for both sports, which will give us some room for manoeuvre,\\\" Paris 2024 told Reuters.\", \"from\": 3854, \"to\": 3999, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3991, \"end\": 3998, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 0.9999999995875442, \"rank\": 4.1263960595774015e-10, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Furthermore, the decision-making process will be more refined and precise than ever, as the Eau de Paris laboratory will be analysing the water twice a day.\\\"\", \"from\": 4001, \"to\": 4159, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4094, \"end\": 4106, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eau_de_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Eau de Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eau_de_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eau_de_Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If, despite the postponements, the competition cannot take place, the marathon swimming event will take place at the reserve site of Vaires-sur-Marne, where rowing and canoeing events are held.\", \"from\": 4161, \"to\": 4354, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The triathlon will be turned into a duathlon.\", \"from\": 4356, \"to\": 4401, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"REUTERS  Pollution  Swimming  N levels  E-paper  Newsletters  Podcasts  RSS Feed  About Us  Terms & Conditions  Personal Data Protection Notice  Need help?\", \"from\": 4402, \"to\": 4557, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4402, \"end\": 4409, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"REUTERS\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 4474, \"end\": 4482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"RSS Feed\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reach us here.\", \"from\": 4558, \"to\": 4572, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertise with us\", \"from\": 4574, \"to\": 4591, \"entities\": []}]}"